---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import GetAppButton from "@components/GetAppButton.astro";
import Page from "@layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page
  title="Box Timer – Free CrossFit Timer App for iPhone"
  description="Free CrossFit timer app for iPhone and iPad. AMRAP, EMOM, For Time, and Tabata timers with loud beeps and a gym-style display. No ads, no subscriptions."
  url="https://boxtimer.app/crossfit-timer/"
  canonical="https://boxtimer.app/crossfit-timer/"
>
  <Container innerClass={"flex-col items-center"}>
    <div class="w-full sm:w-9/12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans font-bold">
        Free CrossFit Timer for iPhone
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl font-light text-zinc-500 mt-4">
        The ad-free timer that looks and works like the clock at your box
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 mb-16">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-crossfit-top" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        A gym clock in your pocket
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Box Timer was built to replicate the large wall clock at a CrossFit box.
        The digital display, the beeps at round transitions, the simple
        controls — everything is designed so you can set up a WOD in seconds
        and focus on the workout, not the app.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Whether you are doing an AMRAP at the gym, an EMOM in your garage, or
        a For Time workout while traveling, Box Timer handles all the standard
        CrossFit timer formats.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        CrossFit workout types and how to set them up
      </h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">AMRAP (As Many Rounds As Possible)</h3>
      <p class="mb-2">
        Set a time cap and do as many rounds of a given workout as you can.
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-1 mb-6">
        <li>Tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong> and select <strong>Down</strong></li>
        <li>Set your time cap (e.g. 20 minutes)</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">For Time</h3>
      <p class="mb-2">
        Complete a prescribed workout as fast as possible with a running clock.
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-1 mb-6">
        <li>Tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong> and select <strong>Up</strong></li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Start</strong></li>
        <li>Stop the timer when you finish the workout</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">EMOM (Every Minute On the Minute)</h3>
      <p class="mb-2">
        Perform reps at the start of each minute, rest for whatever time
        remains.
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-1 mb-6">
        <li>Tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong> and select <strong>Interval</strong></li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rounds</strong> (e.g. 10), <strong>Work</strong> to 1:00, and <strong>Rest</strong> to 0:00</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Tabata</h3>
      <p class="mb-2">
        8 rounds of 20 seconds work, 10 seconds rest.
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-1 mb-6">
        <li>Tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong> and select <strong>Interval</strong></li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rounds</strong> to 8, <strong>Work</strong> to 0:20, and <strong>Rest</strong> to 0:10</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Why Box Timer for CrossFit?
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3">
        <li>
          <strong>Gym-style display</strong> — Digital numbers with a glow
          effect that looks like the clock on the wall at your box. Choose
          between Standard, Minimal, or High Contrast themes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>All WOD formats</strong> — AMRAP (countdown), For Time
          (count up), EMOM, and Tabata (intervals) in one app.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Loud beeps</strong> — Round transitions and countdown
          warnings so you hear the clock even under a barbell.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Works with your music</strong> — Beeps play over your music
          without stopping playback.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Workout history</strong> — Every WOD is saved. Pin and name
          your frequent workouts. Reload settings with one tap.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Free, no ads</strong> — No subscriptions, no premium tier,
          no ads. Built by a CrossFitter, for CrossFitters.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-16 mb-8">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-crossfit-bottom" />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-16">
        <strong>Related:</strong>
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/emom-timer/"
          >Free EMOM Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/tabata-timer/"
          >Free Tabata Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/box-timer-vs-smartwod/"
          >Box Timer compared to SmartWOD</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <Footer />
</Page>
